- 4 ans d'expérience en tant qu'assistante personnelle(y compris des gens haut placés) ;
- double nationalité ( Biélorusse/ Française) ;
- Trilingue: Russe (langue maternelle), Anglais (TOEFL Ibt:98), Français ( TEF: C1/C2) ;
- Diplôme de Master dans les Affaires Européen (droit, comptabilité, gestion des projets);
- l'expérience solide dans l'organisation de différents types d'événements (voyages, concerts privés, soirées thématiques, séminaires anniversaires, sortie culturelles etc);
- l'expérience dans le gestions des relations avec les fournisseurs et différents types des prestataires; 
- l'expérience dans la réservation des hôtels, voitures, visites dans différents pays (Japon, Canada, Etats-Unis etc);
- sens inné du tact et de la diplomatie; 
- capacité à communiquer facilement;
- flexible, autonome et réactive.

13 ans de protection rapprochée De ministres et De chef d'État ;
12 ans en temps que chauffeur de direction et entretien d'une clinique privée ;
Vous verrez mon C.V. parle pour moi,
En attendant je suis à votre disposition pour un entretien.
Sincères salutations distinguées.

After working successfully for almost 10 years as a Compliance Officer, I acquired a good knowledge of KYC rules, Compliance and AML regulation and policies, Monegasque, French, European and US legislation; FIDES program, FATCA legislation, AML and research software. 
During 2 years in Compagnie Monégasque de Banque I was a Supervisor of AML/CFT section of the Compliance Department and SICCFIN Correspondent. I was in charge of development of the AML software in CMB and in CFM, group Crédit Agricole Indosuez Private Wealth Management. 
During my working career that began in 2004, I’m used to do the numerous Personal Assistant tasks as well :
•	devising and maintaining office systems, including data management and filing;
•	arranging travel, visas and accommodation;
•	screening phone calls, inquiries and requests, and handling them when appropriate;
•	meeting and greeting visitors at all levels of seniority;
•	organizing and maintaining diaries and making appointments;
•	dealing with incoming email, faxes and post, often corresponding on behalf of the manager;
•	taking dictation and minutes;
•	carrying out background research and presenting findings;
•	producing documents, briefing papers, reports and presentations;
•	organizing and attending meetings and ensuring the manager is well prepared for meetings;
•	liaising with clients, suppliers and other staff.
I followed numerous in-house training courses linked to Banking Activity, AML, Combating the Financing of Terrorism, Corruption and E-security and I am used to cooperating with almost all the departments of the bank. 
In  2009 I had an important training with IntellEval in Monaco concerning Anti-Money Laundering, Combating the Financing of Terrorism and Corruption with  89.03% of good results, one of the 3 best results.

I acquired the profound investigation and monitoring skills and I am also in charge of the development of the AML reports for the AML Department.

Being a native Russian and Ukrainian speaker, I am also perfectly bilingual in English and French and specialized in the clients, banks, brokers from the East European Countries. 

I am fond of Finance, Banking, Communication and Foreign Languages, which can be traced from my educational background and professional experience.

I am a hard-working, rigorous, discrete, conscientious and dynamic person with strong work ethic and sense of responsibility. 

Team player, strategic thinking and quick learner as well as motivated by complicated assignments, I am also a good negotiator and listener. I am able to work under pressure and prioritize tasks.

I hope my credentials will interest you and I look forward to hearing from you.
Thank you for your time and consideration.

-fait preuve de rigueur, de méthode et d'organisation;
-grand sens de l'empathie;
discréte;
-patiente et calme.

